          "description": "I gave the woman at reception the (perhaps im biased) incredibly relevant feedback that the self check- in screen is poorly placed because whoever is sitting in the first two chairs of the waiting room can see the screen and patient input containing sensitive information (full name, email, DOB, last four digits of social security number). She said \u201ci know but there is nothing we can do because of the wires\u201d and that \u201cpeople shouldn\u2019t be looking at other peoples screens\u201d. I would hope a place would take the privacy of their patients more seriously because in the end, the people who want to do harm don\u2019t care about the wire or about whether or not one \u201cshould\u201d stare at the screen while other people are checking in.\n\nps the chairs of the waiting room are all more than 1ft apart. they could be pushed to one side.\n\nWhat a tragedy apathy is.",
