          "description": "Be aware that if you are a NYU employee using their health insurance, the UHC Langone copay waiver does not apply. Depending on your coverage expect a 200+ bill two months after your last appointment. This office specifically bills it this way: instead of an office setting where it would be covered they enter themselves as outpatient HOSPITAL.\nAdditionally, these services are going to be covered by your \"Habilitative Services - Physical therapy\" benefits. They can be found under \"Coverage & Benefits\" if you need to recall them. These services are covered with a $40 copay per session with no deductible. So that means is even if you have not met the deductible yet this service would still be covered with a $40 copay per session.\nI feel like they knew all these things and still pushed me to have more appointments than I needed.\nFrom a care perspective I waited almost an hour my first visit and was rushed out in every subsequent visit.\nSuper strange. I will never go here if I need any sort of similar care.",
